---
title: Souk-ulent Chicken Tagine with Apricot, Flaked Almonds and Cooling Yoghurt (5 MEAL)
description: Head Chef Patrick recently went off on another of his ‘research’ (AKA holiday) trips. This time it was to the exotic souks of Marrakech. A lot of people seemed interested in the rugs and teapots but our trusty chef took one for the team and spent his whole trip testing food to inspire our future menus. This little number was one of those dishes. Where shall we send him next? Answers on Facebook please!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/553e444a6ced6ef9758b4568.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/553e444a6ced6ef9758b4568.pdf
cuisine: Middle Eastern
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 675 kcal
  fat: 9 g
  saturated fat: 1 g
  carbohydrates: 115 g
  protein: 32 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/souk-ulent-chicken-tagine-553e444a6ced6ef9758b4568
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
---

Peel the @onion{1}(peeled), slice in half through the root and then thinly cut widthways
into half moon shapes. Peel and dice the @sweet potato{1}(diced) and @carrot{1/2}(diced)
into about 1cm cubes. Finely chop the @garlic cloves{2}(finely chopped) and roughly
chop the @dried apricots{3}(roughly chopped).

Chop the @British chicken thighs{3} into bite sized pieces. Heat 1 tbsp of
@olive oil{1%tbsp} in a pan on medium-high heat. Once hot add the chicken and
season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for around ~{5%minutes} until
cooked through then remove until later.

Heat 1 tbsp of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in the same pan on medium heat and cook the
onions and garlic until soft. Add the @ras-el-hanout{1.5%tsp} and stab the whole
@red chilli{1}(stabbed a few times) a few times before adding to the pan. Fry
gently for ~{1%minute}.

> The more you stab the chilli the hotter the final dish will be.

Add half the @chicken stock{1/2%stock pot} with 500ml of boiling water to the pan
together with the chicken, sweet potato, carrot and apricots. Season with
@salt{1/4%tsp} and and few grinds of @pepper{} to taste. Cover with a #lid{} and
cook on a medium heat for ~{10%minutes}, then uncovered for ~{10-15%minutes}.

Boil 250ml of water with the remaining @chicken stock{1/2%stock pot}. Add in your
@couscous{1} and cover the #pot{} tightly. Take off the heat and leave to rest
for ~{5%minutes}.

> Be exact with the amount of water to prevent soggy couscous!

Finely chop the @mint{2}(finely chopped) and @flat leaf parsley{2}(finely chopped)
and mix all of the mint and two-thirds of the parsley into the couscous. Add
@olive oil{1/2%tbsp}, juice of @lemon{1/2}(juiced) and mix with a #fork{} to
separate the grains.

> Test for seasoning and add as required.

Toast the @flaked almonds{2}(toasted) in a dry #frying pan{} over a medium heat
until they are golden brown.

Mix the @Greek style natural yoghurt{4%tbsp} with the juice of another quarter of
a lemon and a pinch of salt and pepper. Serve the tagine on a bed of couscous
topped with the almonds, a dollop of the yoghurt and the remaining chopped
parsley.